refs.EndpointResponse$Address: The address or token of the endpoint as provided by your push provider (e.g. DeviceToken or RegistrationId).
refs.EndpointResponse$ApplicationId: The ID of the application associated with the endpoint.
refs.EndpointResponse$CohortId: A number from 0 - 99 that represents the cohort the endpoint is assigned to. Endpoints are grouped into cohorts randomly, and each cohort contains approximately 1 percent of the endpoints for an app. Amazon Pinpoint assigns cohorts to the holdout or treatment allocations for a campaign.
refs.EndpointResponse$CreationDate: The last time the endpoint was created. Provided in ISO 8601 format.
refs.EndpointResponse$EffectiveDate: The last time the endpoint was updated. Provided in ISO 8601 format.
refs.EndpointResponse$EndpointStatus: The endpoint status. Can be either ACTIVE or INACTIVE. Will be set to INACTIVE if a delivery fails. Will be set to ACTIVE if the address is updated.
refs.EndpointResponse$Id: The unique ID that you assigned to the endpoint. The ID should be a globally unique identifier (GUID) to ensure that it is unique compared to all other endpoints for the application.
refs.EndpointResponse$OptOut:
Indicates whether a user has opted out of receiving messages with one of the following values:

ALL - User has opted out of all messages.

NONE - Users has not opted out and receives all messages.
refs.EndpointResponse$RequestId: The unique ID for the most recent request to update the endpoint.
refs.EndpointSendConfiguration$BodyOverride: Body override. If specified will override default body.
refs.EndpointSendConfiguration$RawContent: The Raw JSON formatted string to be used as the payload. This value overrides the message.
refs.EndpointSendConfiguration$TitleOverride: Title override. If specified will override default title if applicable.
refs.EndpointUser$UserId: The unique ID of the user.
refs.EventStream$ApplicationId: The ID of the application from which events should be published.
refs.EventStream$DestinationStreamArn:
The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon Kinesis stream or Firehose delivery stream to which you want to publish events.
 Firehose ARN: arn:aws:firehose:REGION:ACCOUNT_ID:deliverystream/STREAM_NAME
 Kinesis ARN: arn:aws:kinesis:REGION:ACCOUNT_ID:stream/STREAM_NAME
refs.EventStream$ExternalId: The external ID assigned the IAM role that authorizes Amazon Pinpoint to publish to the stream.
refs.EventStream$LastModifiedDate: The date the event stream was last updated in ISO 8601 format.
refs.EventStream$LastUpdatedBy: The IAM user who last modified the event stream.
refs.EventStream$RoleArn: The IAM role that authorizes Amazon Pinpoint to publish events to the stream in your account.
refs.GCMChannelRequest$ApiKey: Platform credential API key from Google.
refs.GCMChannelResponse$ApplicationId: The ID of the application to which the channel applies.
refs.GCMChannelResponse$Credential: The GCM API key from Google.
refs.GCMChannelResponse$Id: Channel ID. Not used. Present only for backwards compatibility.
refs.GCMChannelResponse$Platform: The platform type. Will be GCM
refs.GCMMessage$Body: The message body of the notification, the email body or the text message.
refs.GCMMessage$CollapseKey: This parameter identifies a group of messages (e.g., with collapse_key: "Updates Available") that can be collapsed, so that only the last message gets sent when delivery can be resumed. This is intended to avoid sending too many of the same messages when the device comes back online or becomes active.
refs.GCMMessage$IconReference: The icon image name of the asset saved in your application.
refs.GCMMessage$ImageIconUrl: The URL that points to an image used as the large icon to the notification content view.
refs.GCMMessage$ImageUrl: The URL that points to an image used in the push notification.
refs.GCMMessage$JsonData: The data payload used for a silent push. This payload is added to the notifications' data.pinpoint.jsonBody' object
refs.GCMMessage$RawContent: The Raw JSON formatted string to be used as the payload. This value overrides the message.
refs.GCMMessage$RestrictedPackageName: This parameter specifies the package name of the application where the registration tokens must match in order to receive the message.
refs.GCMMessage$SmallImageIconUrl: The URL that points to an image used as the small icon for the notification which will be used to represent the notification in the status bar and content view
refs.GCMMessage$Sound: Indicates a sound to play when the device receives the notification. Supports default, or the filename of a sound resource bundled in the app. Android sound files must reside in /res/raw/
refs.GCMMessage$Title: The message title that displays above the message on the user's device.
refs.GCMMessage$Url: The URL to open in the user's mobile browser. Used if the value for Action is URL.
refs.ImportJobRequest$ExternalId: A unique, custom ID assigned to the IAM role that restricts who can assume the role.
refs.ImportJobRequest$RoleArn: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an IAM role that grants Amazon Pinpoint access to the Amazon S3 location that contains the endpoints to import.
refs.ImportJobRequest$S3Url:
A URL that points to the location within an Amazon S3 bucket that contains the endpoints to import. The location can be a folder or a single file.
The URL should follow this format: s3://bucket-name/folder-name/file-name

Amazon Pinpoint will import endpoints from this location and any subfolders it contains.
refs.ImportJobRequest$SegmentId: The ID of the segment to update if the import job is meant to update an existing segment.
refs.ImportJobRequest$SegmentName: A custom name for the segment created by the import job. Use if DefineSegment is true.
refs.ImportJobResource$ExternalId: A unique, custom ID assigned to the IAM role that restricts who can assume the role.
refs.ImportJobResource$RoleArn: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an IAM role that grants Amazon Pinpoint access to the Amazon S3 location that contains the endpoints to import.
refs.ImportJobResource$S3Url:
A URL that points to the location within an Amazon S3 bucket that contains the endpoints to import. The location can be a folder or a single file.
The URL should follow this format: s3://bucket-name/folder-name/file-name

Amazon Pinpoint will import endpoints from this location and any subfolders it contains.
refs.ImportJobResource$SegmentId: The ID of the segment to update if the import job is meant to update an existing segment.
refs.ImportJobResource$SegmentName: A custom name for the segment created by the import job. Use if DefineSegment is true.
refs.ImportJobResponse$ApplicationId: The unique ID of the application to which the import job applies.
refs.ImportJobResponse$CompletionDate: The date the import job completed in ISO 8601 format.
refs.ImportJobResponse$CreationDate: The date the import job was created in ISO 8601 format.
refs.ImportJobResponse$Id: The unique ID of the import job.
refs.ImportJobResponse$Type: The job type. Will be Import.
refs.ImportJobsResponse$NextToken: The string that you use in a subsequent request to get the next page of results in a paginated response.
refs.Message$Body: The message body. Can include up to 140 characters.
refs.Message$ImageIconUrl: The URL that points to the icon image for the push notification icon, for example, the app icon.
refs.Message$ImageSmallIconUrl: The URL that points to the small icon image for the push notification icon, for example, the app icon.
refs.Message$ImageUrl: The URL that points to an image used in the push notification.
refs.Message$JsonBody: The JSON payload used for a silent push.
refs.Message$MediaUrl: The URL that points to the media resource, for example a .mp4 or .gif file.
refs.Message$RawContent: The Raw JSON formatted string to be used as the payload. This value overrides the message.
refs.Message$Title: The message title that displays above the message on the user's device.
refs.Message$Url: The URL to open in the user's mobile browser. Used if the value for Action is URL.
refs.MessageBody$Message: The error message returned from the API.
refs.MessageRequest$RequestId: Original request Id for which this message is delivered.
refs.MessageResponse$RequestId: Original request Id for which this message was delivered.
refs.MessageResult$UpdatedToken: If token was updated as part of delivery. (This is GCM Specific)
refs.QuietTime$End: The default end time for quiet time in ISO 8601 format.
refs.QuietTime$Start: The default start time for quiet time in ISO 8601 format.
refs.SMSChannelResponse$ApplicationId: The unique ID of the application to which the SMS channel belongs.
refs.SMSChannelResponse$CreationDate: The date that the settings were last updated in ISO 8601 format.
refs.SMSChannelResponse$Id: Channel ID. Not used, only for backwards compatibility.
refs.SMSChannelResponse$ShortCode: The short code registered with the phone provider.
refs.SMSMessage$Body: The message body of the notification, the email body or the text message.
refs.Schedule$EndTime: The scheduled time that the campaign ends in ISO 8601 format.
refs.Schedule$StartTime: The scheduled time that the campaign begins in ISO 8601 format.

refs.SegmentImportResource$ExternalId: A unique, custom ID assigned to the IAM role that restricts who can assume the role.
refs.SegmentImportResource$RoleArn: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of an IAM role that grants Amazon Pinpoint access to the endpoints in Amazon S3.
refs.SegmentImportResource$S3Url: A URL that points to the Amazon S3 location from which the endpoints for this segment were imported.
refs.SegmentResponse$ApplicationId: The ID of the application to which the segment applies.
refs.SegmentResponse$CreationDate: The date the segment was created in ISO 8601 format.
refs.SegmentResponse$LastModifiedDate: The date the segment was last updated in ISO 8601 format.
refs.SegmentsResponse$NextToken: An identifier used to retrieve the next page of results. The token is null if no additional pages exist.
refs.SendUsersMessageRequest$RequestId: Original request Id for which this message is delivered.
refs.SendUsersMessageResponse$RequestId: Original request Id for which this message was delivered.
refs.TreatmentResource$TreatmentDescription: A custom description for the treatment.
refs.TreatmentResource$TreatmentName: The custom name of a variation of the campaign used for A/B testing.
refs.WriteCampaignRequest$Name: The custom name of the campaign.
refs.WriteCampaignRequest$SegmentId: The ID of the segment to which the campaign sends messages.
refs.WriteCampaignRequest$TreatmentDescriptio: A custom description for the treatment.
refs.WriteCampaignRequest$TreatmentName: The custom name of a variation of the campaign used for A/B testing.
refs.WriteEventStream$DestinationStreamArn:
The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon Kinesis stream or Firehose delivery stream to which you want to publish events.
 Firehose ARN: arn:aws:firehose:REGION:ACCOUNT_ID:deliverystream/STREAM_NAME
 Kinesis ARN: arn:aws:kinesis:REGION:ACCOUNT_ID:stream/STREAM_NAME
refs.WriteEventStream$ExternalId: The external ID assigned the IAM role that authorizes Amazon Pinpoint to publish to the stream.
refs.WriteEventStream$RoleArn: The IAM role that authorizes Amazon Pinpoint to publish events to the stream in your account.
refs.WriteTreatmentResource$TreatmentDescript: A custom description for the treatment.
refs.WriteTreatmentResource$TreatmentName: The custom name of a variation of the campaign used for A/B testing.
